Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.80, 13. Name, Klearchos. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0160.03.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0408)
